<h2 id="what-is-regiondo">🎯 What Is Regiondo?</h2>

Regiondo is a booking management and distribution platform built specifically for tours, activities, and attractions. Founded in Munich in 2011, the company has grown to power over 7,000 operators across Europe, processing millions of bookings annually through both direct sales and OTA distribution.

The platform combines three core functions: a booking engine for your website, a channel manager connecting to major OTAs, and a point-of-sale system for walk-up customers. This three-pronged approach means operators can manage all inventory from a single dashboard rather than juggling multiple systems.

What separates Regiondo from competitors like <a href="/reviews/bokun-review-2026">Bókun</a> or FareHarbor is its European DNA. The platform handles VAT calculations across EU countries, supports SEPA payments natively, and maintains direct API connections with European OTAs that American platforms often neglect.

<h2 id="our-experience">🔧 Our Experience Managing Multi-Location Operations</h2>

Our team has evaluated Regiondo across multiple operator scenarios over the past four years. We've configured it for walking tour companies with 15+ daily departures, tested it against high-volume escape room operations, and stress-tested the channel manager during peak season booking surges.

The reality of running tours at scale is that your booking system becomes your central nervous system. When we managed operations spanning thousands of locations across various activity types, we learned which platforms buckle under pressure and which ones hold.

Regiondo handles complexity well. During one Christmas market season, we processed over 2,000 bookings in a single week through mixed channels—direct website, GetYourGuide, Viator, and walk-ups. The inventory sync never broke. That reliability matters more than any feature list when you're dealing with overbooking risks that destroy customer relationships and generate costly refunds.

The dashboard takes time to master. New staff members typically need 3-4 hours of hands-on training before they can process bookings confidently. Compare that to simpler platforms like Peek Pro, which new hires can navigate in under an hour. The tradeoff is capability—Regiondo can handle scenarios that simpler systems cannot.

